<HEADLINE> Lebed Stresses Role of Russia in Ending Yugoslav Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The governor of Russia's
Krasnoyarsk region, Alexander Lebed, said here on Wednesday that
Russia is the only country which can help the United States save
its face in the Yugoslav crisis.
</P>
<P>
``Russia can play a decisive role, all the world has known
it,'' said Lebed after having a meeting with former French
Interior Minister Charles Pasqua.
</P>
<P>
He said that the visits to Moscow by U.S. Assistant Secretary
of State Strobe Talbott, the U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan,
and several other Western personalities for the Yugoslav crisis
showed that Russia has returned to the international scenery.
</P>
<P>
Lebed, who is former Russian presidential security advisor and
an army hero in the Afghanistan War, said that the NATO bombings of
Yugoslavia ``have yielded nothing and will yield nothing,'' while
the Serbs have won ``a moral victory.''
</P>
<P>
He said that Russia will not send arms to Yugoslavia, but will
not follow the Western oil embargo.
</P>
<P>
Lebed and Pasqua also issued a communique calling for ``a
common step'' by the French and Russian governments to let the
United Nations Security Council play a major role in solving the
Kosovo problem.
</P>
<P>
Pasqua, who will lead a separate list of candidates from the
Gaullist Rally for the Republic party in the European elections to
be held in June, is one of the few French political personalities
who oppose the NATO airstrikes on Yugoslavia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
