<HEADLINE> Clinton Urges Congress Approve Funding for Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 28 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
Wednesday urged Congress to swiftly approve six billion U.S.
dollars to pay for the continuing bombing of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Speaking after the president briefed lawmakers at the White
House on the air campaign against Yugoslavia, Clinton also urged
the lawmakers to resist Republican-led efforts to double his
request.
</P>
<P>
"We must get a Kosovo funding measure passed and to my desk
now," Clinton said as the House was debating a challenge to his
authority to widen the military campaign. 
</P>
