<HEADLINE> New Zealand Pledges Support for U.N. Effort on Cyprus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- New Zealand's Minister of Foreign
Affairs and Trade Don Mckinnon said here on Wednesday that his
country support the ongoing U.N. process on Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
Speaking after a meeting with Cyprus' Foreign Minister Ioannis
Kasoulides, Mckinnon expressed hope that the Cyprus issue will
soon be solved.
</P>
<P>
"One would like to see the Cyprus problem resolved, the issue
has been around for a long time," he said.
</P>
<P>
Mckinnon said New Zealand and Cyprus has given each other a lot
of support in the U.N., in the Commonwealth, and regional
institutions.
</P>
<P>
Mckinnon said he discussed the Kosovo crisis with Kasoulides.
</P>
<P>
"Like everyone else", he said, "we do hope to see a
sustainable solution to what is happening in Kosovo, in the
Balkans".
</P>
<P>
Kasoulides said he and Mckinnon had the opportunity to discuss
a variety of issues of common interest.
</P>
<P>
He expressed appreciation for Mckinnon's contribution to the
Commonwealth.
</P>
<P>
Mckinnon, who arrived here on Tuesday for a three-day visit,
has announced his candidacy to become Secretary-General of the
Commonwealth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
