<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central Bank Warns Against Dangers of Village </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A press release issued by the central bank said Wednesday that
those village banks are not banks and therefore their existence is
a breach of law.
</P>
<P>
Those organizations have never been authorized to do banking
business in Uganda, the press release added, explaining that the
word "bank" can only be used by a bank and the authority to use
the word can only be sought and granted by the Ministry of
Finance.
</P>
<P>
The central bank warned villagers and enterprises not to
deposit their money in these so called banks because they are
illegal.
</P>
<P>
Since these village organizations are not financial
institutions approved by the Ministry of Finance, the bank will
not be responsible for the activities of these village banks.
</P>
<P>
The village banks, which do not have qualifications required of
banks, offer extraordinary high interest rates to attract
depositors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
