<HEADLINE> NATO Says Civilian Damage Inevitable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April, 28 (Xinhua) -- A NATO spokesman Wednesday said
civilian damage is inevitable while confirmed the reports that a
residential area in Surdulica, Southern Yugoslavia, had been
bombed by NATO's aircraft, which causing death of 17 people and
hundreds of houses.
</P>
<P>
NATO spokesman Jamie shea told reporters in a statement that
NATO "cannot completely exclude the possibility of harm to
civilians, or to civilian property, during a conflict such as this
one."
</P>
<P>
During a daily news briefing at NATO headquarters here in
Brussels, a NATO military spokesman, General Marani, said only one
bomb caused the civilian damage. But some reports said at least
two bombs hit civilian targets during Tuseday's NATO airstrikes.
</P>
</TEXT>
