<HEADLINE> France: Purging of Draskovic Confirms Existence of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 28(Xinhua) -- France said on Wednesday that the
purging of Yugoslav Vice Prime Minister Vuk Draskovic seems to
confirm the existence of an opposition to the policy of President
Slobodan Milosevic.
</P>
<P>
``We could ask if the declarations of Draskovic were made in
his personal name or if they engaged the authorities of Belgrade.
His purging brings the answer,'' said French Foreign Ministry
spokeswoman Anne Gazeau-Secret.
</P>
<P>
The spokeswoman said that the purging of Draskovic also seems
to confirm that an opposition to the ``disastrous'' policy of
Milosevic is coming to the surface and that the ``signs of split
are appearing'' in Belgrade.
</P>
<P>
Draskovic was sacked on Wednesday by Yugoslav Prime Minister
Momir Bulatovic for having expressed views ``contradicting the
positions of the government.''
</P>
<P>
A former opposer of Milosevic, Draskovic is the leader of the
rightwing Renewal of Serbia party.
</P>
<P>
While criticizing Milosevic for not telling the truth about the
massive exodus of Kosovars to the Yugoslav people, Draskovic has
called for a compromise with NATO and allowing an international
peacekeeping force in Kosovo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
