<HEADLINE> Mozambican Journalists Slam NATO for Bombing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The Mozambican National
Association of Journalists issued a statement here Wednesday,
condemning the NATO for bombing the Yugoslavian Television Station
last week, killing over 10 reporters.
</P>
<P>
The Mozambican journalists voiced full solidarity with their
Yugoslavian colleagues, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
It deplored that free expression which the West has been
chanting for years was violated as the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization bombed the Yugoslavian television station. The
Yugoslavian people have been denied their rights to have access to
news telling the truth.
</P>
<P>
"We shout out to condemn this act (of bombing) which has made
us retreat to the era when the law of the jungle reigns," it
stressed.
</P>
<P>
"If it (the bombing attack) had been launched by a poor
country, such action would surely entail cut on aid and would be
openly denounced by the West," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The Mozambican media offered comprehensive coverage of the NATO
bombing on Yugoslavia, but there had been few comments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
