<HEADLINE> Mogadishu Heavy Fighting Terrifies Somalis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Heavy fighting erupted between
rival militiamen at the dangerous Bakara junction of Mogadishu
Wednesday afternoon, terrifying people of the Somali capital.
</P>
<P>
The exchange of heavy and small gunfire between militiamen
belonging to the Islamic militiamen of South Mogadishu and those
loyal to faction leader Mohamed Qanyareh Afrah still continues in
the area.
</P>
<P>
There are no exact number of casualties available. However,
hospital sources confirmed four deaths and five wounded of the
Islamic militiamen.
</P>
<P>
Eyewitnesses who just escaped the scene, however, mentioned
five deaths including militiamen supporting Afrah.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, eyewitnesses said that more than seven battle wagons
and about 200 heavily-armed men are involved in the fighting for
control of the strategic Bakara junction just south of the main
business center of Mogadishu Bakara market.
</P>
<P>
The reason for the fighting is said to have related to an
agreement between the Islamic courts and businessmen in Bakara
market over the responsibility of the security in the market and
the surrounding areas three days ago. 
</P>
