<HEADLINE> Russian Communist Party Chief Condemns U.S. Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The chief of the Russian Communist
Party Gennady Zyuganov said on Wednesday that the long-term
strategy of the United States is to divide Europe.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the press when attending a conference of the
Council of Europe in Strasbourg, eastern France, Zyuganov also
condemned the NATO bombings of Yugoslavia, describing them as
``acts of immoral barbarity.''
</P>
<P>
``There is not any difference of mentality between the American
youths who shot their classmates in a school in Colorado and the
pilots who bomb the targets in Yugoslavia,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
He was referring to a shooting rampage which took place in a
high school near Denver, the United States, last week.
</P>
<P>
``It is not in the interests of the United States that Europe
be united, that the Council of Europe represent the human rights
and that euro exist,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that there will be no winner in the war against
Yugoslavia, and that Europe is faced with the problem of ethnic
Albanian refugees from Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
``The Danube river is paralyzed, the refugees will be dispersed
in the cities and countries of Europe, and that will only provoke
a rising of terrorism,'' he added. 
</P>
