<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of African
Unity (OAU) said wednesday that it will send a mission to four
African countries to assess refugee situation there.
</P>
<P>
An OAU press release issued here Wednesday said that following
a recommendation by the bureau of the OAU Commission on Refugees,
OAU Secretary General Salim Ahmed Salim has authorized a mission
of the commission to go to Angola, the Democratic Republic of
Congo (DRC), Tanzania and Zambia.
</P>
<P>
The press release said, "the objective of the mission is to
assess the situation on the ground and determine to what extent
the OAU can assist these countries, which are affected by exodus
of thousands of refugees as a result of the ongoing war in the
DRC."
</P>
<P>
According to the press release, the bureau of the OAU
Commission on Refugees, which is responsible for monitoring and
assessing the situation of refugees, returnees and displaced
persons in Africa, held a meeting here Tuesday and expressed
concern over the serious negative consequences of the war in the
DRC on the environment and the socio-economic situation in the
region.
</P>
<P>
"The bureau also deplored the fact that the international
community was focussing on the plight of refugees elsewhere, at a
time when the African continent is experiencing a complex
refugee's crisis," the press release said. 
</P>
