<HEADLINE> South Africa's Producer Inflation Edges Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 28 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's year-on-year
producer inflation was 5.5 percent in March, half a percentage
point higher than the corresponding annual rate of 5.0 percent in
February, Statistics South Africa said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
From February to March the Producer Price Index (PPI) increased
by 0.3 percent, while the seasonally adjusted index increased by
0.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The annual increase of 5.5 percent in the PPI was mainly due to
annual increases in the price indices for locally produced
commodities, the national statistical bureau said.
</P>
<P>
The rate increase for locally produced commodities was 4.2
percentage points, compared with 1.3 percentage points for
imported commodities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
