<HEADLINE> Kuwait TV Collects 13 Million Dollars For Kosovars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 28 (Xinhua) -- A two-day relief campaign
launched by Kuwait Television Station (KTV) Monday raised over 13
million U.S. dollars for the Kosovo refugees, official Kuwait
News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The campaign, titled "the International Solidarity Day with
the Kosovo People", was previously planned for one day and had to
be extended for anther day as the turnout for the humanitarian
activity was much higher than anticipated, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Abdul Mohsen Al-Bnai, who is in charge of the KTV educational
programs, said that during the working hours on the first day of
the campaign, up to 7 million dollars were collected.
</P>
<P>
Many people rushed to the headquarters of the Information
Ministry for donation, Al-Bnai said.
</P>
<P>
Some Kuwaiti women even donated their personal jewelry and sale
of land lots in Lebanon, he said.
</P>
<P>
A woman, who contacted the KTV from Qatar, offered to construct
72 residential units for the Kosovo refugees taking shelter in
Macedonia, the official added.
</P>
<P>
Kuwaiti officials said some of the collected money would be
used in setting up housing units for the refugees, while the rest
would be used for buying needed relief materials or forwarded
directly to the Kosovars.
</P>
<P>
Kuwaiti Emir Jaber Al-Ahmad Al-Sabah has ordered another plane
for transferring relief aid donated by the society and the Kuwaiti
people.
</P>
<P>
Early this month, Kuwait had already airlifted several batches
of relief supplies to the refugee-stricken countries in the Balkan
region. Kuwaiti volunteers helped distribute the supplies there.
</P>
<P>
On April 6, Emir Jaber, on behalf of the royal family, donated
1 million dollars for the Kosovo people.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of thousands of Kosovars have fled their homes to
neighboring countries since the North Atlantic Treaty Organization
(NATO) launched intensive air strikes against Yugoslavia on
March 24. 
</P>
</TEXT>
