<HEADLINE> WHO Worried About Kosovo Refugee Health Condition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The World Health Organization
regional director for Europe, Eiric Jo Asvall, said Wednesday that
he is worried about the danger of an epidemic among the Kosovo
refugees as the Summer is drawing close.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting with Albanian Prime Minister Pandeli Majko, Asvall
said that "The fact that no epidemic has occurred so far is very
important, but the danger of an epidemic spread increases as the
Summer is drawing close."
</P>
<P>
"That is why the preliminary measures to avoid these diseases
is a necessity," the WHO director said.
</P>
<P>
He said the WHO will deliver a long-term assistance to help
Albania cope with the emergency situation arising from the arrival
of more than 360,000 Kosovo refugees.
</P>
<P>
Majko said that his government has taken strict measures to
control the health assistance delivered for the Kosovo refugees.
</P>
<P>
Asvall also held a working meeting with Albanian Health
Minister Leonard Solis.
</P>
<P>
Their talks centered on the current health situation of the
Kosovo refugees in Albania.
</P>
<P>
Asvall is scheduled to visit the northern Albanian city of
Kukes, where there are still more than 100,000 Kosovo refugees.
</P>
</TEXT>
