<HEADLINE> Sichuan Center Opens In Britain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Sichuan, one of China's most
populous provinces, opened a UK office, called the Sichuan Center,
here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the inauguration ceremony, Li Dachang, vice
governor of Sichuan Province, said: "The Sichuan Center is a key
part of our effort to promote closer relations and business links
between Sichuan and the UK."
</P>
<P>
Peter Nightingale, China-Britain Business Council chief
executive, said: "We anticipate that the Center will stimulate
business between the UK and Sichuan and enable British companies
to make more effective business links with an important province
of China."
</P>
<P>
Li Dachang is visiting the UK with a delegation of some 60
officials and business people from Sichuan province. This is the
largest business group to visit the UK from the province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
