<HEADLINE> Tension Depopulates Border Villages in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The tension in the border areas
between Albania and Yugoslavia has caused depopulation of villages
in the north Albanian district of Tropoja.
</P>
<P>
"Over 4,000 inhabitants of the Prush, Zogaj, Zherke and Lucidol
villages have been evacuated," Secretary of the District Council
Isa Kuliqi was quoted by the Albanian news agency ATA as saying
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Kuliqi said that only a few of the villagers have moved to
Bajram Curri town and the others have gone to stay with their
relatives in other parts of the district.
</P>
<P>
The evacuation started on March 24 after NATO began air strikes
against Yugoslavia, which have continued for more than a month.
</P>
<P>
Albania has alleged that Serb army in Kosovo have been
attacking Albanian border villages with mortars and cannons, which
Yugoslavia denies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
