<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2100GMT, April 28 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- The Israeli Foreign Ministry has lodged a protest
against a resolution adopted by the United Nations Human Rights
Commission, which supports Palestinian self-determination on the
basis of the U.N. partition resolution 181 adopted in 1947.
</P>
<P>
With European support, the commission adopted on Tuesday in
Geneva the resolution on the Palestinian issue, which also calls
for the right of Palestinian refugees to return home.
(BC-Israel-Protest)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- The Israeli military Wednesday closed the Area "A"
of Jenin in the West Bank following a shooting incident in which
an Israeli Defense Force (IDF) soldier was wounded, according to a
senior Palestinian Security officer.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli military announced the closure of Area "A" and
turned it into a military zone shortly after the shooting incident
Wednesday noon, the officer said. (BC-Israel-Jenin Closure)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has
warned Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat not to declare an
independent Palestinian State on May 4 this year.
</P>
<P>
Talking to reporters before meeting with foreign diplomats here
on Wednesday afternoon, Netanyahu said the peace process can
move forward if Arafat refrains from doing so.
(BC-Israel-Netanyahu-Palestine)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
