<HEADLINE> German Neo-Nazis Kill 16 Since 1990: Gov't Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The German government said Wednesday
in a report that 16 people have been killed in German neo-Nazi
attacks since the country's unification in 1990.
</P>
<P>
The killings were carried out with an anti-Semitic, racist or
neo-Nazi ideological motive, and a total of six people were
convicted for these crimes or cases of attempted murder, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
However, the government admitted its figure of 16 deaths caused
by neo-Nazis might be incomplete. Because of Germany's strict
privacy laws, the authorities may have erased data kept in police
computers.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, an annual report from the Interior Ministry
said totally 28 people were killed in far-right attacks from 1991
through 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
