<DOCNO> XIE19990429.0065 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Decides to Suspend Beef Imports From U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission said
here Thursday that it formally decided to suspend imports of beef
and bovine liver from the United States as of June 15.
</P>
<P>
This action was taken to protect consumers' health in 15 member
states of the European Union (EU) following the discovery by an
independent study of residues of certain synthetic growth
promoting hormones in beef and bovine livers imported from the
U.S., the EU executive branch said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The commission also decided to check 100 percent of U.S. beef
and bovine liver imports. The European Commission said its
Standing Veterinary Committee supports this action.
</P>
<P>
But the commission said both decisions will be reviewed on the
basis of evolution of the situation and guarantees supplied by the
competent authorities of the United States.
</P>
<P>
The EU commissioner of Agriculture and Rural Development, Franz
Fischler, said that the commission is ready to work closely with
the U.S. authorities to resolve this problem and welcomed the fact
that the first round of discussions between the two sides last
week were constructive.
</P>
<P>
However, the commissioner insisted that the decisions could not
be changed until the European Union is satisfied that its "Hormone
Free Cattle Program" is operating effectively, ensuring that these
imports were produced without the use of hormones. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
