<HEADLINE> Palestinian Students Protest Against Delaying </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Some 100 Palestinian students
held demonstration Thursday to protest against the decision of the
Palestinian leadership to postpone a statehood declaration.
</P>
<P>
The students from the Palestinian Bir Zeit University, which
lies to the north of the major West Bank city of Ramallah, also
clashed with Israeli soldiers when marched on a main road between
Ramallah and the town of Bir Zeit.
</P>
<P>
Israel Radio said that the clashes broke out after the
students stoned Israeli vehicles on the road, which is under
Israel's control. But no injuries were reported.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian Central Council voted on Thursday morning to
delay a decision on statehood declaration until after Israeli May
17 general elections.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat had repeatedly hinted that he
will declare an independent state on May 4 when the five-year
interim self-rule period enshrined in the Oslo peace agreements
expires.
</P>
<P>
But dozens of world leaders have urged him to hold off the move
to avoid playing in the hands of Israeli hard-line Prime Minister
Benjamin Netanyahu in the coming elections.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu also has threatened to take tough actions against the
possible Palestinian statehood proclamation, including annexing
parts of the West Bank that are still under Israel's control.
</P>
</TEXT>
