<HEADLINE> Australian, Chinese Harbors to Increase Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The Australian harbor of Bunbury
signed a contract of intention here today to develop a "sister
port" relationship with the port of Zhapu in northern Zhejiang
Province.
</P>
<P>
John Willinage, president of the board of directors of Bunbury
Harbor, said that sisterhood between the two harbors will help
increase economic and trade between Zhejiang and northern
Australia.
</P>
<P>
He suggested that the two harbors conduct extensive cooperation
in ocean-going shipping and exchanges of harbor technology.
</P>
<P>
Zhapu is the only port in northern Zhejiang, and is only 100
kilometers from Hangzhou, the provincial capital, and Shanghai,
China's largest economic and financial city. The port handled 7.4
million tons of cargo last year. 
