<HEADLINE> Horti-Expo to Open as Scheduled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
KUNMING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Everything is ready for the
opening of the China '99 Kunming International Horticultural
Exposition, which will open as scheduled tomorrow, a provincial
official announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the third meeting of representatives of
participating countries and organizations, Cai Jingtai, deputy
secretary-general of the Yunnan provincial government, said that "
construction of the Expo site has been completed; the gardens and
exhibition halls of all participating countries and international
organizations have been laid out well; the days for participating
countries and organizations to celebrate their participation have
been fixed; and Yunnan has already created favorable conditions
and is ready to cope with an anticipated big influx of tourists,"
said Cai, who is also the deputy representative of the Chinese
government to Expo '99.
</P>
<P>
Hailed as the last grand world exposition in this century,
Expo '99 is attended by 95 countries and international
organizations. The Expo site is to open officially to visitors at
noon on May 1.
</P>
<P>
The meeting announced the establishment of a College of
Commissioners-General of Sections and Steering Committee, which is
put in charge of settling disputes and promoting cooperation
between the organizing committee and the participating countries
and international organizations.
</P>
<P>
Members of the Steering Committee include representatives from
China, France, Peru, Chile, Egypt, Australia, the United Nations
Development Program and the International Network for Bamboo and
Rattan. 
</P>
