<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fighting in S. Mogadishu Kills At Least 7 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, April 29 (Xinhua) -- At least seven people were
killed and more than 17 others including civilians wounded during
the early hours of the fighting between rival militiamen in south
Mogadishu Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Heavy and sporadic exchange of gunfire still continues between
three Islamic courts in south Mogadishu and the militiamen loyal
to faction leader Mohamed Qanyarch Afriah.
</P>
<P>
The fighting which has lasted for two days is very much
concentrated over the control of the strategic strong point of
Bakara junction, at the southern end of Mogadishu's main business
center, where the militiamen of Afrah are still in control.
</P>
<P>
The serious shooting has made the main Wadnaha street almost
deserted with the public transport and pedestrians having come to
a halt.
</P>
<P>
The fighting has similarly forced the closure of many stores and
shops in fear of the fighting in the market. . Both sides are
using more than six double barrel ant-aircraft heavy machine guns
and about a dozen battle wagons mounted with different heavy
machine guns supported by hundreds of militiamen.
</P>
<P>
Intensive peace talks between religious leaders, clan elders
and businessmen from the warring sides are now continuing in south
Mogadishu in an effort to contain the hostility which seems to be
degenerating into a clannish war.
</P>
<P>
According to sources close the meeting, both sides have
accepted a formal cease-fire. But a difficult point is over an
argument that the Islamic courts should pull their militiamen out
of the new positions around the former Hawlwadag police station
which they had occupied two nights ago.
</P>
<P>
Apart from all these peace negotiations, the fighting is
further spreading to new areas in the capital.
</P>
<P>
Trouble is not confined to Mogadishu alone, but the town of
Baidoa, some 245 kilometers south of the capital city, has also
experienced night armed confrontations between militiamen from the
Rahanwein Resistance Army (RRA) and others loyal to Hussein
Mohamed Aidid.
</P>
<P>
At least nine people were killed and more than 15 others were
wounded when the RRA fighters had infiltrated into the town,
shelling the militia
bases of Aidid there. 
</P>
</TEXT>
