<HEADLINE> Arabs, Switzers Keen on Boosting Ties: AL Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Arab League (AL) Secretary General
Esmat Abdel-Meguid said in Geneva on Thursday that the Arabs and
Switzers share a desire to promote cooperation in all domains,
especially in economy and trade.
</P>
<P>
Abdel-Meguid made the remarks in an interview with Egypt's
Voice of Arab radio over telephone. He described the Arab-Swiss
relations as "good."
</P>
<P>
Abdel-Meguid arrived in Switzerland Tuesday to attend a meeting
of the Arab-Swiss Chamber of Commerce and Industry on the occasion
of the 25th anniversary of its establishment.
</P>
<P>
When addressing the meeting, the league chief stressed the
Arabs' keenness to achieve a just and comprehensive peace in the
Middle East, the Cairo-based radio said.
</P>
<P>
He also called on the Swiss side to support the Arab cause and
bolster trade with the Arab countries, the radio added.
</P>
<P>
Abdel-Meguid said he held talks with Swiss officials on ways of
enhancing economic and trade relations between Arab countries and
Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
The peace talks between Arab countries and Israel, which began
in 1991, are stalled due to Israel's intransigent policy in the
peace process. 
</P>
