<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> International Labor Day Marked in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Vice President Hu Jintao extended
cordial greetings to all workers at a meeting held today marking
International Labor Day on May 1.
</P>
<P>
Hu, also a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Communist Party of China Central Committee,
delivered a keynote address at the celebration which was attended
by more than 3,000 people at the Great Hall of the People.
</P>
<P>
Hu spoke highly of the great contributions the Chinese workers
have made to the Chinese revolution, construction and reform. He
said that the year 1999 is of special significance in Chinese
history, urging all workers to carry on their fine traditions, and
make greater efforts to deepen reform, promote economic
development, and maintain stability.
</P>
<P>
Reform is a powerful motive force to the socialist cause, and
also the key policy of decisive importance to China's future.
Improving state-owned enterprises is not only a major issue for
the national economy and long-term development, but also a major
political issue that concerns the prospects of the socialist
system, the vice president said.
</P>
<P>
He called on workers to advance in the face of difficulties,
and to unswervingly support the Party and the government in their
efforts to reform and restructure the state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Stability is the basic prerequisite for reform and development,
and without stability nothing can be done, and the achievements we
have made could be lost, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
He called on workers to dearly cherish the good political
situation of stable public order and social unity, to further
enhance their awareness of socialist democracy and law, and to
fight any attempts to jeopardize national unity, state security,
or social stability.
</P>
<P>
The vice president encouraged workers to learn more about
modern science and technology and improve themselves in order to
adapt to the fast-changing world and the socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the workers' status as masters in enterprises
of public ownership will never be allowed to change, adding that
workers in non-state sectors are also masters of the State, and
their rights and interests must be protected.
</P>
<P>
Some 1,000 outstanding workers and collectives were presented
with awards at today's celebration. 
</P>
