<HEADLINE> More Than 2,000 Journalists Converge to Kunming Horticultural Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- With goblets flashing from hand
to hand and a frequent exchange of toasts, Chinese and foreign
journalists coming to Kunming, capital of southwest China's Yunnan
Province, to cover the coming '99 International Horticultural
Exposition had a good taste of local people's hospitality this
evening.
</P>
<P>
The organizing committee of the horticultural show, scheduled
to open here Friday evening, gave a grand reception for
journalists from all over the world for this gardening gala.
According to the Expo Organizing Committee, the number of Chinese
and foreign journalists has beat the 2,000 mark.
</P>
<P>
"The people of Yunnan have always been famous for their
hospitality," said Xue Zegao, spokesman and press center director
of the Kunming Expo '99 in a toast to the 1,000-strong journalists
present.
</P>
<P>
The feast, in the form of a buffet, abounds with delicious food
with Yunnan local flavor, wines and soft drinks. "I have never
attended such a sumptuous reception for journalists before," said
one of the guests.
</P>
<P>
In his toast, the spokesman reiterated the theme and aim of the
horticultural show: to promote the harmonious co-existence between
man and nature in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
"Your visit and your work will surely further elaborate the aim
and the theme," he noted.
</P>
<P>
The exposition organizers once only expected the arrival of
some 1,600 journalists. But the press center has been bombarded by
a great influx of applications, which still kept coming in even
after the April 15 deadline.
</P>
<P>
The last world exposition of this century and the first to be
hosted by China, or by a developing country, the Kunming Expo '99
has drawn 95 participants worldwide, including 69 countries and 26
international organizations. 
</P>
