<HEADLINE> Egyptian President Invited to Visit Portugal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Portugal has invited Egyptian
President Hosni Mubarak to pay a visit to the country, Portuguese
Foreign Minister Jaime Gama said here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after a meeting with Mubarak, Gama said
he delivered an invitation message to Mubarak from Portuguese
President Jorge Sampaio and Prime Minister Antonio Guterres.
</P>
<P>
The meeting "provided a good chance" for him to hear Mubarak's
views on the Egyptian-Portuguese relations, the Egyptian-African
ties and the Middle East situation as well, he said.
</P>
<P>
Gama, who arrived here on Wednesday for a three-day visit, said
he also discussed with Mubarak various ways of enhancing
cooperation between Egypt and the European Union and the Euro-Med
partnership.
</P>
<P>
Portugal will assume the rotating presidency of the EU in
January.
</P>
<P>
The EU and its 15 member states are Egypt's major trade
partners. Egypt and the EU are negotiating for a partnership
agreement, which will outline future bilateral cooperation in
industry, agriculture and trade.
</P>
<P>
The EU and 12 Mediterranean countries, including Egypt, kicked
off the Euro-Med partnership process in 1995 when the countries
held a meeting in Barcelona, Spain, to seek cooperation in the
political, economic, social and security fields. 
