<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Djibouti Prime Minister in Kunming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"The regional conflicts are all associated with national or
religious friction but the fundamental cause lies in the existence
of hegemonism and power politics," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks during a meeting with Djibouti Prime
Minister Barkat Gourad Hamadou in this capital of southwest
China's Yunnan Province this afternoon. The two leaders had a
friendly and cordial conversation.
</P>
<P>
China has always persisted in the Five Principles of Peaceful
Co-Existence advocated by the older generation of Chinese leaders,
including Mao Zedong, Zhou Enlai and Deng Xiaoping, Jiang noted,
stressing that "all nations, big or small, strong or weak, rich or
poor, are equals."
</P>
<P>
"We hope that the next century would be one of peace, stability
and prosperity", Jiang stated.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese President extended a warm welcome to Prime
Minister Hamadou who has come to China for the opening ceremony of
the '99 Kunming International Horticultural Exposition scheduled
on Friday and wished his China tour a complete success.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin said that the relations between China
and Djibouti based on the Five Principles of Peaceful Co-Existence
have always developed smoothly over the past two decades since the
two countries established diplomatic ties, despite changes in the
international and domestic situation.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two countries have constantly strengthened
their political, economic and cultural cooperation and have always
sympathized with and supported each other, adding that China is
satisfied with all these.
</P>
<P>
Hamadou spoke highly of the friendly relations of cooperation
between his country and China and expressed the hope that such
relations would be further reinforced by the China visits by
Djibouti president and by his current visit.
</P>
<P>
He thanked the Chinese government for inviting him to the
opening ceremony of the Kunming horticultural exposition.
</P>
