<HEADLINE> 8 Filipinos Killed in Mayor-Vice Mayor Clash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 29 (Xinhua) -- At least eight people were killed
while another was critically wounded in a clash between the
southern Philippines' Sumisip municipal mayor and vice mayor
Wednesday afternoon, Philippines News Agency (PNA) said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The agency said the clash began when a group supporting
municipal Vice Mayor Hataman broke into the Sumisip municipal
building and started shooting at the men of Mayor Tahajid who was
holding a conference inside.
</P>
<P>
Tahajid's group retaliated and initially killed three of
Hataman's men. The encounter continued until late Wednesday
afternoon and the death toll rose to eight from both sides.
</P>
<P>
The military and police were later sent to the municipal hall
of Sumisip to pacify the bloody encounter.
</P>
<P>
According to PNA, police are investigating the incident to
determine exactly the motive behind the encounter. 
