<HEADLINE> Tibet Aid Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Most of the 62 Tibet aid projects
set up by the Chinese government have been completed and the rest
are expected to be completed within this year, said Li Dezhu,
Minster of the State Nationalities Affairs Commission today.
</P>
<P>
Started in 1994, after the third working meeting on Tibet held
by the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China and the
State Council, these major projects cover a wide field including
museums, schools, power stations and highways.
</P>
<P>
Li, presiding over a seminar over the publication of a picture
and article album featuring the projects here today, said that
they have played an important role in Tibet's social and economic
development.
</P>
<P>
He said that China's central government has always paid full
attention to Tibet's development, and the successful construction
of the 62 projects have once again proved this.
</P>
<P>
According to him, the projects represent the largest and most
effective aid for Tibet since the founding of the People's
Republic of China in 1949.
</P>
<P>
Top Chinese leaders Jiang Zemin, Li Peng and Li Ruihuan wrote
inscriptions respectively for the picture and article album.
</P>
</TEXT>
