<HEADLINE> Li Peng Stresses NPC's Supervision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- China's top legislator Li Peng
stressed here today that supervision by the legislature is still
very weak and in urgent need of improvement and enhancement.
</P>
<P>
Li, chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress (NPC), made the statement at the four-day NPC session,
which concluded this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The general thinking of the NPC's guidelines for this year is
to place equal emphasis on legal supervision and the formulating
of laws, while enhancing and improving supervisions, and
supporting the major policy of reforms, developments and stability,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Li noted that first of all, efforts must be made to raise the
importance of the supervisory role played by the NPC.
</P>
<P>
"The NPC's supervision constitutes an important part of the
country's efforts at ruling the country by laws," he said.
</P>
<P>
Its aim is to help the administrative and judicial departments
work according to the laws, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The top legislator stressed that the NPC should first of all
work for the party's central work, and focus its efforts on major
social issues.
</P>
<P>
This year, the NPC will inspect the implementation of four laws
concerning air pollution, forestry, the quality of products and
compulsory education.
</P>
<P>
"In the meantime, we should also put emphasis on the
effectiveness of supervision," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Li also revealed that the top legislature is planning to draft
a law on the NPC's supervision, which could help regulate and
improve NPC's performance in this aspect. 
</P>
</TEXT>
