<HEADLINE> Quality Checks on China's Construction Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The State Bureau of Quality and
Technical Supervision announced here today it will launch a two-
month-long quality check of construction materials nationwide
starting May 3.
</P>
<P>
The geographical focus of these checks will be in Hebei, Henan,
Hubei, Hunan, Anhui, Jiangsu, Jiangxi, Zhejiang, Sichuan, Shandong,
Heilongjiang provinces and the city of Shanghai, according to Zhu
Mingxian, deputy director of the bureau.
</P>
<P>
"The main targets will be construction materials and builders
merchants, and a number of important construction sites, which
have been the source of large numbers of customer complaints,"
said Zhu.
</P>
<P>
The materials to be checked will include cement, concrete bar,
bricks, decorating items, coatings, fire-fighting equipment and
water-proof goods, among others. Packaging, security certificates
and quality certificates will also come under the bureau's
scrutiny, Zhu added.
</P>
<P>
The aim of the exercise is to crack down on any illegal
activities in the process of production, distribution and
utilization.  
</P>
</TEXT>
