<DOCNO> XIE19990429.0161 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> High Quality Test Results Made Known </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- China's State Bureau of Quality
and Technical Supervision today expressed satisfaction with the
quality of products made by large state-owned and foreign-funded
enterprises in the first quarter this year.
</P>
<P>
A series of quality tests conducted by the bureau shows that a
relatively high ratio of these products have met strict targets
and some have even been given a 100 percent approval rate.
</P>
<P>
The bureau announced the results today, after selectively
examining more than 2,000 products of more than 1,500 enterprises.
The average qualification rate is 77.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
The test showed that 93 percent of the products made by large
enterprises are qualified while the products of medium-sized and
small enterprises are given a qualification rate of 83 percent and
70 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
According to the tests, 86.5 percent of the products of the
state-owned enterprises and 87 percent of those of the foreign-
funded ones are qualified, while private firms only have 36.6
percent of their products pass the tests.
</P>
<P>
Among the 42 kinds of products under examination, color
kinescope, car radial-type tires and petrol are 100 percent
qualified. The main problems lie in the quality of some
agricultural capital goods which are not ideal, and petrol
products are expected to fully meet the standards laid down for
environmental protection.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
