<HEADLINE> NPC Session Discusses Draft on Macao Troops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The drafting of a law related to
the garrisoning of troops in Macao is necessary and should be
approved as soon as possible, said participants in the ninth
session of China's top legislature today.
</P>
<P>
Liang Guangda, a member of the Standing Committee of the
Chinese National People's Congress (NPC), said the draft is of
great importance to Macao's return to the motherland in December
this year and to the motherland's ultimate unification.
</P>
<P>
"Stationing troops in Macao will not only help maintain social
stability, but will also create a good investment and living
environment there," he said.
</P>
<P>
Liang expressed the hope that the draft will become law in the
near future.
</P>
<P>
Tong Zhiguang, also a member of the committee, said that
stationing troops in the Macao Special Administrative Region is of
symbolic significance to the world.
</P>
<P>
Some members saw much similarity between the draft and the law
concerning stationing troops in Hong Kong, which is being
implemented smoothly there.
</P>
<P>
The draft, which is an improvement over the law on stationing
troops in Hong Kong, will also see smooth implementation, they
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
