<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Tumble on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Share prices tumbled on
Singapore Stock Market Thursday, giving up some of the hefty gains
it made over the past month.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index was down 18.67 points to
1,818.49 at the close, weaker but well off the intraday low of
1,781.25 points.
</P>
<P>
The total volume decreased to 512.63 million shares valued at
647.48 million Singapore dollars (380.83 million U.S. dollars).
Decliners outstripped advancers by 243 to 85 with 110 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The larger block was the 68.80-million stock parcel by the
PohTiong which was transacted at 0.375 Singapore dollars per
share. Poh Lian was the second most heavily traded stock with a
turnover of 15.74 million units. GES was the next which saw 14.93
million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Hwa Hong was the top mover of the day running up 33 cents to
close at 1.74 Singapore dollars. NatElec rose 20 cents to 5.80
Singapore dollars. SP Fin w99 gained 19.5 cents to end at 0.84
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 continued to be the biggest loser
of the day shedding 70 cents to 20.70 Singapore dollars. SPH sank
60 cents to finish at 23.00 Singapore dollars. Venture lost 55
cents to end at 9.35 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that the market index had earlier tumbled 3.1
percent but the rebound in Hong Kong helped the local market to
cut some of its losses.
</P>
<P>
They said this is the first serious correction since the latest
market rally began, noting bank and property shares were the first
to rise and the first to get hit on profit-taking.
</P>
<P>
Dealers attributed the correction to growing concerns over the
stretched valuation which will allow a more sustained correction.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
