<HEADLINE> NATO's Bombing of Yugoslavia Blocks Disarmament (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese People's Association
for Peace and Disarmament (CPAPD) expressed here today great
indignation and strong condemnation over the United States and
NATO's brutality against the Yugoslav people.
</P>
<P>
"The military actions of NATO, headed by the United States, is
escalating at present," said an announcement by CPAPD. "NATO's air
strikes against Yugoslavia have caused heavy casualties and loss
of property in Yugoslavia and millions of refugees have lost their
homes."
</P>
<P>
Since March 24 when NATO began its air strikes against
Yugoslavia, the Chinese people, who always love peace and oppose
aggression, have expressed a sense of justice and sympathy by
showing their deep concern over the developing situation,
condemning NATO's military actions in various ways and expressing
sympathy and support for the Yugoslav people, the announcement
said.
</P>
<P>
"Chinese people firmly support the stand of opposing the war
and peaceful settlement of the Kosovo issue which is maintained by
the Chinese government and President Jiang Zemin, " it noted. "We
also support their efforts to this end. "
</P>
<P>
It pointed out the NATO, which is conducting military actions
against a sovereign state, has violated the international law, and
its act of bullying a small country by using the strongest
military strength and most advanced weapons contradicts natural
human justice.
</P>
<P>
CPAPD cited NATO's act as an anti-humanitarian one with the
excuse of safeguarding humanitarianism, and aggression on the
pretext of settling ethnic conflicts.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990429.0166 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NATO's Bombing of Yugoslavia Blocks Disarmament (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NATO's action embodies the hegemonism and power politics, and
the "gunboat policy", which has completely gone against peace and
the development trends of the world.
</P>
<P>
After the Cold War, the international situation began to ease,
and with the dismantling of the Warsaw Pact, NATO lost the
foundation for its existence, it said.
</P>
<P>
However, the western countries headed by the United States has
stubbornly stuck to the Cold War mentality by expanding and
strengthening military alliances in Europe and Asia, and the
United States has also largely increased its military expenditure
and speeded up its research of hi-tech weaponry including missile
defense systems.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the United States and its military allies have
increased their military interference in other countries' internal
affairs in order to spread their own values and pursued their own
selfish interests in the region and in the world at large, while
safeguard their hegemony, according to the announcement.
</P>
<P>
"The act, which goes against historic trends, has seriously
threatened international security, shattered the international and
regional strategic balance, and brought a great threat to world
peace and development in the 21st century," it said. "This should
make other peoples maintain a sharp vigilance over these actions."
</P>
<P>
The current situation in Kosovo is resulted from the wanton
interference of the western countries into the internal affairs of
Yugoslavia by imposing their will on others and disregarding the
sovereignty and territorial integrity of the country, the
announcement said.
</P>
<P>
It continued that NATO's air strikes against Yugoslavia have
trampled on the classical principles enshrined in the UN Charter,
which include: aggression is the most serious crime against peace,
the border of a country is sacred and inviolable, any country can
not interfere in other's internal affairs, and all countries have
the right to guard against splitting.
</P>
<P>
NATO's wanton support of the splitist forces has set a vile
example for international relations, it added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990429.0167 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NATO's Bombing of Yugoslavia Blocks Disarmament (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In fact, the act has thrown away the international organization
and multilateral institution which have been playing the most
important role in maintaining world peace and stability. Therefore,
it has imposed an adverse influence on international relations,
the announcement noted.
</P>
<P>
The military expanse of the United States and its alliance has
also obstructed the disarmament cause and the international
military control, and blocked the development of the world's
economy because it will contain the sound trend of disarmament and
economic development appeared after the Cold War, and it is
possible to cause another round of armament race, it added.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the war has not only seriously damaged the
economy of Yugoslavia, but also brought a heavy burden to the
economies of other countries in the Balkan region and relevant
NATO countries, it noted.
</P>
<P>
"At the turn of the century, peace and development is the
common aspiration of the people in the world and follow the trends
of the time," it said. "Power politics and hegemonism is unpopular.
"
</P>
<P>
In the last month, the large-scale anti-war movements in many
countries in the world, especially in the NATO countries, have
reflected people's opposition to the war and their call for the
peace, it said, adding that urging NATO to halt the military
attack and peacefully solve the Kosovo problem has become the
common aspiration of most people in the world.
</P>
<P>
"We firmly believe that justice will overcome evil and peace
will beat the war," it said. "Justice stands on the side of the
Yugoslav people and the victory will be won by the brave and
glorious Yugoslav people." 
</P>
</TEXT>
