<HEADLINE> ADB Launches Public Bond Issue in Australia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
had launched a 500-million-Australian dollar (about 326.5 million
U.S. dollar) public bond issue in the Australian domestic bond
market, a news release of ADB said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to ADB, the bond issue, launched on Wednesday with a
coupon rate of 5.25 percent per annum payable semiannually and a
maturity date of September 15, 2004, was priced at 99.414 percent
to yield 35 basis points over the 9 percent Commonwealth
Government Bond due on September 15, 2004.
</P>
<P>
This transaction is the ADB's second borrowing in the
Australian dollar domestic bond market. The ADB plans to undertake
domestic Australian dollar bond issues on a regular basis with a
view to building a yield curve. 
</P>
</TEXT>
