<HEADLINE> Foreign Ministry Spokesman on Sino-Russian Border Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- China and Russia have completed
97 percent of border alignment in the eastern section of their
border and all the work of border alignment in western section,
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Sun Yuxi said here today.
</P>
<P>
All this has been set by law through decades of negotiations,
Sun said at a press conference.
</P>
<P>
Only the ownership of two areas has not been defined, and the
two sides have been working for resolving the issue, Sun added.
</P>
<P>
China and Russia share a common border of more than 4,300
kilometers, and the Sino-Russian border issue is left over from
history, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
