ended little changed after lower than expected wages data dampened
the currency's earlier excitement over the prospects for steady
interest rates.
</P>
<P>
Nick Volanakis, treasury manager of Colonial State Bank, said
the Australian currency spiked to an early session high of 65.62
U.S. cents as stop-loss buy orders were triggered, with support
from improved gold and commodity prices.
</P>
