with an agonizing quietness, abandoned to stray dogs and
paramilitary forces patrolling in speeding vehicles on the streets,
according to the few refugees from Pristina who fled to Macedonia
lately. They said that 80 percent of the city's inhabitants have
left, and only the elderly, women and children can still be seen
on the street from 11 o'clock till 13 o'clock buying food.
</P>
