<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Commemorating May 4th Movement by Following Historical Tide (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- With the 80th anniversary of the
May 4th Movement imminent, Shao Huaze, president of the People's
Daily, said today in a full-page article that following the
historical trend of the times is the best way for Chinese people
to commemorate the movement and carry forward its spirit.
</P>
<P>
They must hold high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory,
adhere to the basic line of the Communist Party of China (CPC),
and under the leadership of the Party Central Committee with
Comrade Jiang Zemin at its core, comprehensively carry forward the
great cause of building socialism with the Chinese characteristics
into the 21st century, Shao said.
</P>
<P>
The May 4th Movement, also known as the New Cultural Movement,
was led by Chinese intellectuals, who went with the then tide of
historical development, to pursue democracy and science.
</P>
<P>
It was a great patriotic movement fighting against imperialism
and feudalism, and an inevitable outcome for Chinese people at the
time, Shao said.
</P>
<P>
With the start of the Opium War in 1840, China gradually fell
into a semi-colonial and semi-feudal society, which suffered
fierce domestic political and economic contradictions and
conflicts with imperialists.
</P>
<P>
After the Sino-Japanese War of 1894 -1895, various imperialist
powers were ready to divide up China.
</P>
<P>
At that time, China faced national subjugation and genocide
launched by those powers, Shao said.
</P>
<P>
Many advanced intellectuals struggled to rescue the nation. But
after the failure of the Reform Movement of 1898, led by liberal
intellectuals Kang Youwei and Liang Qichao, and the bourgeois
democratic revolution of 1911, led by Dr. Sun Yat-sen which
overthrew the Qing Dynasty (1644-1911), the Chinese people fell
into dire straits.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990429.0187 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Commemorating May 4th Movement by Following Historical Tide (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It is imperative to have in advance a clear view of the
essential movement of the historical development which resulted in
the May 4th Movement, the article said.
</P>
<P>
To do so, all classes, parties, social groups and individuals
must have a firm command of scientific thinking, recognize and
grasp the law governing social and historical developments, and
combine them with patriotism and the fundamental interests of the
nation and people.
</P>
<P>
Efforts must be made in the following aspects:
</P>
<P>
Firstly, it is essential to have a correct understanding of the
basic contradictions of society.
</P>
<P>
During the May 4th movement, the Chinese people chose Marxism
and socialism, among other then political mainstream thoughts,
only after repeated practice and comparisons.
</P>
<P>
They realized that in China's semi-colonial and semi-feudal
society, where the contradictions between the working masses and
imperial and feudal forces prevailed, it was imperative to launch
a revolution against such forces in order for China to achieve
independence and liberation.
</P>
<P>
All the changes that took place after the May 4th Movement
can't be separated from the deepened understanding of the
essential contradictions of Chinese society.
</P>
<P>
Secondly, it is essential to have a scientific grasp of the
basic national conditions, the article said.
</P>
<P>
The success of China's new democratic revolution lies in the
fact that the Chinese communists led by Chairman Mao Zedong,
guided by Marxism and Leninism, analyzed and understood the
national conditions in a scientific way.
</P>
<P>
They concluded that the Chinese revolution must rely heavily on
the country's overwhelming number of peasants to set up rural
revolutionary bases which would ultimately encircle and conquer
the cities.
</P>
<P>
Only by following this path did the Chinese revolution overcome
numerous difficulties and obstacles, defeating both domestic and
foreign enemies, achieving victory and establishing the People's
Republic of China 50 years ago.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
