<HEADLINE> China Hopes for Permanent Peace in Korean Peninsula </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua)-- China believes that the
establishment of a peace mechanism in the Korean Peninsula through
the four-party talks will serve to maintain peace and stability in
the peninsula and in northeast Asia as a whole, and it is also in
the interests of relevant parties.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Sun Yuxi made the remark
when asked to comment on the fifth round of four-party talks on
the Korean Peninsula issue.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that the four-party talks will achieve gradual
progress, and that a permanent peace in the peninsula will be
realized, as long as all relevant parties maintain patience and
continue their efforts in a practical manner," he said.
</P>
<P>
The fifth round of four-party talks on the Korean Peninsula
issue was held in Geneva from April 24 to 27.
</P>
<P>
Sun said that during the talks, relevant parties engaged in in-
depth discussions about the establishment of a peace mechanism in
the Korean Peninsula and relaxation of the tensions there based on
the progress of the previous talks, and that they promoted
understanding of their respective stances.
</P>
<P>
The four parties agreed that during the next round of talks,
they will continue discussing such substantial issues as the
topics of the working groups, the measures to ease tensions, and
the outline of the future peace mechanism in the peninsula, he
added.
</P>
<P>
However, they still have different views on some issues due to
historical reasons, Sun said, and the attainment of the objectives
of the four-party talks will be a long-term and step-by-step
process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
