<HEADLINE> Foreign Banks Approved To Experiment With RMB Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Asia's financial turmoil will
not alter China's policies to open up its financial sector and the
People's Bank of China (PBOC), the nation's central Bank, will
continue to allow more eligible foreign banks to run RMB business
on a trial basis, said Wu Xiaoling, head of the PBOC Shanghai
Branch at the China 99' Business Summit which ended Wednesday in
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Wu emphasized that China has been persistently implementing
safe finance-opening policies in a proper sequence, adapting the
opening speed to domestic economic growth level and taking into
account financial supervision abilities.
</P>
<P>
Qualified foreign banks will be authorized to experiment with
RMB deals in an increasing number of areas in China, Wu added,
saying that Shanghai is slated to turn into an international
financial center.
</P>
<P>
Wu urged more effort to tighten financial supervision by
drawing up a series of guidelines and to create a good environment
for foreign banks by providing them with training and other
services involved in the Chinese currency business.
</P>
