<HEADLINE> FM Spokesman on NATO's "New Concept" (Details added) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua)-- Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman
Sun Yuxi said here today that at a time when seeking peace is the
common aspiration of the world people, the reinforcement of
military alliance goes against the historical trend.
</P>
<P>
Sun made this remark at today's routine press conference when
asked to comment on NATO's "new concept" and "new strategy" put
forward when it celebrated its 50th anniversary.
</P>
<P>
NATO is the result of the cold war era, and today the world
situation has witnessed profound changes, Sun said, adding that
seeking peace, cooperation and development has become the common
aspiration of all the world people.
</P>
<P>
Under such a background, seeking reinforcement of military
alliance and expanding its external military interference function
will produce serious results, he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
To interfere in a sovereign state's internal affairs or try to
seek solutions to regional and international conflicts by
surpassing the UN Charter and universally recognized norms of the
international law is not only harmful to the world peace and
security, but also runs counter to the historical trend, the
spokesman stressed.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that during the post-cold war era, how
European security should be guaranteed and what kind of role NATO
should play are questions not only faced by European countries,
but also concerned by the world community.
</P>
<P>
Recently, NATO, surpassing the UN, conducted military
interference in a sovereign state like Yugoslavia, and such an
action seriously violates the UN Charter and the international law,
and is strongly opposed by all peace-loving countries and peoples,
he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
