<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Steps Up Control on Foreign Exchange Income </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- China's State Administration of
Foreign Exchange (SAFE) announced today that, together with the
Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC), it
has formulated provisional procedures to check on the foreign
exchange income of foreign trade firms.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the SAFE said that effective supervision on the
foreign exchange income and payment of foreign trade enterprises
is an important component in China's foreign exchange
administrative system as the prevention of illegal practices in
foreign exchange income and payment can help maintain balanced
international payments.
</P>
<P>
According to the procedures, which will take effect on May 1,
the check will be focused on the foreign exchange collection rate
of exports, and foreign trade firms will be graded according to
their foreign exchange collection rate.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that the SAFE and the MOFTEC will use policy
and banking measures to reward or punish enterprises in line with
their gradings.
</P>
<P>
The procedures will be applicable to both foreign trade
companies and productive and other enterprises with import and
export rights, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
