<HEADLINE> FM Spokesman: Cox's Report Groundless </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The allegations by the U.S. side,
especially Cox's report on the so-called espionage case, have no
factual basis, and are "sheer fabrication with ulterior motives",
a Foreign Ministry spokesman said here today.
</P>
<P>
Sun Yuxi made the remark when asked to comment on a report that
is said to be released and declassified early next month by the
committee of the U.S. congressional representative Christopher Cox,
in which there is alleged conclusive evidence that the Chinese
government continues to conduct espionage in the U.S.
</P>
<P>
"Leaders of the Chinese government have solemnly declared that
China has never stolen any technology or conducted espionage," Sun
said. "The allegation that China steals nuclear weapon technology
is absolutely groundless."
</P>
<P>
Sun also denied that China is behind the alleged theft of U.S.
nuclear weapon secret.
</P>
<P>
If there is secret leaked out of the U.S. laboratory, then it
is only business of their own, Sun said, adding that so it is the
business of the U.S. to strengthen its security measures. 
</P>
