<HEADLINE> Draft Amendments to Highway Law Not Adopted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- China's top legislative body, the
Standing Committee of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC),
did not adopt the draft amendments to the Highway Law at its ninth
meeting here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The number of votes for the draft amendments is only one vote
fewer than the required number for approval.
</P>
<P>
A number of the Standing Committee members voted against the
draft amendments for fear that the adoption of the draft
amendments would increase farmers' burdens, according to sources
at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The amendments to the Highway Law were made to pave the way for
the reform of replacing the highway toll with taxes.  
</P>
