<HEADLINE> Tender Announced for Suez Canal Tunnel: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 29 (Xinhua) -- An international tender has been
announced for building another car tunnel under the Suez Canal,
the Egyptian Gazette newspaper reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The tunnel is a strategic project that links the Sinai
Peninsula with the valley of the northern Kantara area, Minister
of Transport and Communications Soliman Metwalli was quoted as
saying on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The three-kilometer tunnel will be located 18 kilometers south
of Port Said. It will serve the activities of the industrial area
of the port and the Sharq Port Said Harbor currently under
construction, Metwalli said.
</P>
<P>
Sixteen local and international firms submitted reports
detailing their experience, he said, adding that his ministry has
selected 10 of them for further consideration.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project is estimated at 400 million
Egyptian pounds (about 120 million U.S. dollars), half of which
will be covered by investor groups of the Port Said industrial
area.
</P>
<P>
In return, the groups will collect transit fees of the new
tunnel and have rights to a piece of land near the location.
</P>
<P>
Egypt has built a car tunnel at the middle of the Suez Canal
near Ismailia, 110 kilometers east of Cairo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
