<HEADLINE> More Efforts For Sustained Economic Growth: Economists(1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- China needs to improve its
financial services by developing a diversified financial system to
sustain the growth of its national economy, according to an
article analyzing the issue in Thursday's China Securities Daily.
</P>
<P>
Economists pointed out that existing problems including a weak
domestic market, declining exports and falling commodity prices
will be better addressed by promoting financial services.
</P>
<P>
China's pro-active fiscal policies paid off in the first
quarter of 1999, but will need to play an ongoing and important
role in the long term, according to the analysis reflecting the
views of a group of research institutions, including the
macroeconomics desk under the Chinese Academy of Social Sciences.
</P>
<P>
China's gross domestic product (GDP) grew by 8.3 percent in the
first quarter, well above the targeted 7.0 annual growth rate.
</P>
<P>
During the period, industry's value-added output increased by
10.1 percent year on year, and the growth in sales volume of
retail commodities between January and February rapidly reached 8.
1 percent achieving 520 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
However, major indicators for economic growth in March went
below that of earlier months, according to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
A healthy growth of the light industry and private sectors is
of crucial importance under such circumstances when the
accelerated state investment aimed to stimulate domestic demand
has flowed instead to infrastructure construction and the state-
owned sector, economists said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
