<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT April 29 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Two NATO planes crashed Wednesday in Macedonia
after being hit by Yugoslav anti-aircraft fire, the official
Tanjug news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
A NATO plane crashed in the western Macedonia after exploding
in the sky while the other crashed in a Macedonian village near
the border with Yugoslavia, Tanjug quoted a Pristina radio station
as saying. (Belgrade-NATO)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Yugoslav Prime Minister Momir Bulatovic Wednesday
sacked Deputy Prime Minister Vuk Draskovic for "openly opposing
the government's position and undermining its credibility", the
Ministry of Information said.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference held on Tuesday to mark the seventh
anniversary of the founding of the Yugoslav Federation, Draskovic,
who assumed the deputy premiership on January 22, accused the
Yugoslav ruling party, the Social Party of Serbia, of
strengthening dictatorship by taking advantage of the current war
status. (Yugoslavia-Prime Minister-Dismissal)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Serbian President Milan Milutinovic and Kosovo's
ethnic Albanian leader Ibrahim Rugova on Wednesday signed a joint
statement in Pristina on seeking a peaceful solution to the Kosovo
issue.
</P>
<P>
The two also agreed in the statement on the need for an
imminent establishment of a temporary government in Kosovo,
reports reaching here said. (Yugoslavia-Kosovo-Statement)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WARSAW -- Poland on Wednesday sent a company of 140 infantries
to Albania to safeguard the NATO command there.
</P>
<P>
The company, the first group of troops of Poland as a new NATO
member sent for a mission abroad since NATO started bombing
Yugoslavia on March 24, is made up of professional soldiers,
volunteers, doctors, Albanian and Serb interpreters and priests,
the state news agency reported. (Polish Troops-Albania)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
OTTAWA -- A 14-year-old boy opened fire with a gun at a high
school in Alberta, western Canada, Wednesday, killing one student
and seriously injuring another.
</P>
<P>
The suspect, a Grade 9 student who quit the W.R. Myers public
high school, shot down two students both 17 years old and was
taken into custody at the scene by the school resource officer,
said the police. (Canada-Shooting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The U.S. House of Representatives voted late on
Wednesday against a resolution in support of NATO's bombing of
Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The resolution was rejected on a 213-213 tie vote. Earlier, the
House voted 249 to 180 to limit President Bill Clinton's ability
to widen the Kosovo war, demanding the president to get
congressional approval before deploying ground troops. (US-
Yugoslavia-House)
</P>
