<HEADLINE> European Swimming Championships to Be Held in Istanbul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The 1999 European Swimming
Championships will be held in Istanbul in July.
</P>
<P>
The European Swimming Federation (LEN) said in a statement on
Wednesday that the championships is slated for July 22-Augsut 1 in
Turkey's largest city despite concerns over safety at the
competition.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that four federation members had expressed
concern over security in Turkey after a spate of bombing attacks
in Istanbul and other cities by Kurdish rebels.
</P>
<P>
A series of bombing attacks have been launched by Kurds after
Abdullah Ocalan, leader of the Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) was
captured in Kenya in mid-February.
</P>
<P>
According to the statement, an investigation into the
precautionary measures taken showed that Turkey would be able to
hold the swim meet in complete safety.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish government has taken strict security measures to
prevent possible terrorist attacks throughout Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The championship will be held at the Atakoy Olympic Swimming
Pool and will include both swimming and diving. 
</P>
</TEXT>
