<DOCNO> XIE19990429.0272 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: ABCs of Macao SAR Basic Law (61) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Following is part 61 of a
question and answer series on the Basic Law of the Macao Special
Administrative Region (MSAR).
</P>
<P>
Can long-term prosperity and stability in Macao be maintained
after its return to China?
</P>
<P>
There is no doubt that Macao will be able to maintain long-term
prosperity and stability after its return.
</P>
<P>
In terms of policies, the basic policy that the Chinese
Government pursues on Macao is that of "one country, two systems".
This policy has enjoyed extensive support of all Chinese people
including the compatriots in Macao as well as appreciation of the
international community.
</P>
<P>
This is because this policy conforms to both the need for
reform and opening up in China and the actual conditions in Macao.
It is a policy that will serve the long-term interests of China
and its people. It will be a stable and long-term policy and by no
means one of expediency. The Constitution of China and the Basic
Law will guarantee it. In a word, the long-term prosperity and
stability of Macao is ensured by the most reliable policy and
legal safeguards.
</P>
<P>
As to itself, Macao enjoys unique geographical, economic and
cultural advantages and maintains extensive exchanges and links
with many countries and regions. And our Macao compatriots have
had glorious patriotic and hard-working traditions. With the
implementation of the policies of "one country, two systems" and "
Macao people administering Macao", people from all walks of life
in Macao will surely unite more closely, give full play to their
own advantages and with their wisdom, industry and tenacity,
create a more beautiful Macao.
</P>
<P>
In respect to the relationship between the Central Government
and the MSAR, a local administrative region in China enjoying a
high degree of autonomy, the Central Government has the
responsibility and capability to ensure the long-term prosperity
and stability of Macao. The Central Government will vigorously
cooperate with and support Macao in its efforts to promote its
economy and improve its people's livelihood. The deepening of the
reform and opening-up program on the mainland and the steady
increase in China's comprehensive national strength will serve as
an ever stronger guarantee for the long-term prosperity and
stability of Macao.
</P>
<P>
After its return to China, Macao will certainly enjoy a more
splendid future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990429.0273 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China Sea Natural Gas Piped To Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Some 3,700 families in
Shanghai's Pudong New Area have become the first group of
residents in the city to be supplied Wednesday with natural gas
from the East China Sea.
</P>
<P>
Construction work on the natural gas project in the East China
Sea, one of the key state projects during the 1996-2000 period,
has almost been completed after three years of efforts.
</P>
<P>
The project cost more than 6.5 billion yuan (783 million US
dollars) and included construction work on an offshore platform, a
natural gas processing plant, two seabed oil and gas pipes, as
well as related facilities in Shanghai urban areas.
</P>
<P>
The project's daily supply capacity of natural gas to Shanghai
is expected to rise from the current 300,000 cubic meters to 1.2
million cubic meters by the end of the year, making the gas supply
accessible to all residents in Pudong New Area.
</P>
<P>
Citizens living on the west bank of the local Huangpu River
will also gradually be supplied with the "green" energy.
</P>
<P>
With the wider use of natural gas, old coal gas plants in
Shanghai will be gradually closed down or renovated.
</P>
<P>
Oil explored from the sea had been piped to Shanghai by the end
of last year.  
</P>
