<HEADLINE> Central American Labor Ministers Meet in Nicaragua </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The 14th meeting of the Labor
Ministers of Central American countries was held here Wednesday to
discuss the issues concerning employment.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was held to analyze the reality and experience of
the countries on the issues of the employment market, employment
policies, immigration, occupational health and the well-being of
workers, Nicaraguan Labor Minister Wilfredo Navarro said in his
opening speech.
</P>
<P>
"To achieve this, it will require an integrated effort on three
aspects: technical progress, productive employment and investment
in human resources," he said.
</P>
<P>
He urged the labor ministers of the region to strengthen their
roles as protectors of the fundamental rights of workers and be
ready to meet the fresh needs of the workers and employers.
</P>
<P>
The ministers will also discuss under-employment, regional
strategy on employment policies and the macro-economic system in
Central America.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was attended by labor ministers from Belize, Panama,
Nicaragua and the Dominican Republic. 
</P>
