<HEADLINE> S.Lankan President Declares War on Illicit Liquor, Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan President Chandrika
Kumaratunga has ordered a large-scale war against illicit liquor
and drugs which have plagued the country, the official Daily News
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In line with the order, Inspector General of Police Lucky
Kodithuwakku has instructed his officers to act immediately.
</P>
<P>
"It will be a serious, concentrated war on illicit liquor and
drugs," the newspaper quoted a police spokesman as saying.
</P>
<P>
Some 300,000 Sri Lankans fall victim to narcotic drugs and 8
billion rupees (114 million U.S. dollars) go to the pockets of
drug dealers annually, said a latest study.
</P>
<P>
Kodithuwakku stressed the importance and urgency of eliminating
the threat. He told a high-powered police conference that they
should go all out in the matter, adding that the president had
assured there would be no political influence to protect the wrong
doers.
</P>
<P>
A special unit will be set up at police headquarters to monitor
the progress of the effort.
</P>
<P>
The presidential order follows the recommendations of a
committee appointed by the president on the extent of drug use in
the country and on preventive measures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
