<HEADLINE> Brazil Calls for New World Financial System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANIERO, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian President
Fernando Henrique Cardoso on Wednesday urged to establish a new
world financial framework to avoid financial crises.
</P>
<P>
Cardoso told the Industrial Federation of San Paulo after
meeting with visiting Mexican President Ernesto Zedillo that the
loose control of capital flow was detrimental to the world economy.
He deems transparency and tighter controls as priorities in
establishing a new world financial system.
</P>
<P>
He said that Brazil and Mexico, as the two largest economies of
Latin America, should promote trade cooperation, but the major
obstacles were the closed markets and commercial barriers.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the Summit of Latin American and European
countries, scheduled for June 28 and 29 in Rio de Janiero, the
president reiterated the importance of participating actively in
world economic activities. 
