<HEADLINE> EU Enlargement to be Open and Transparent: President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The process of EU enlargement
should be open and transparent as much as possible, according to a
declaration adopted at the seventh meeting of the President of the
European Parliament with presidents of the parliaments of the
countries seeking EU memberships.
</P>
<P>
At a news conference after the meeting on Tuesday, European
Parliament President Jose Maria Gil-Robles said that after the
Helsinki summit at the end of this year, the starting dates for
negotiations on the accession of each applicant state will become
clear.
</P>
<P>
"We do not want to make a distinction between countries of
first and second categories. All countries have the chance to
start the negotiations simultaneously, but each one will be
admitted at a different time," Gil-Robles said. 
</P>
