World Bank have almost cleared the way for the resumption of
lending to Russia, the two monetary organs said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The IMF announced that it had reached an agreement in principle
with Russia on a new economic reform program that will allow it to
resume lending to the country.
</P>
<P>
IMF Managing Director Michel Camdessus said negotiations over
the past few days resolved the major issues that had prevented the
IMF from resuming a lending program cut off in August when Russia
defaulted on billions of dollars in foreign debt. (IMF-WB-Lending-
Russia) 
