<HEADLINE> Two Canadian Students Shot in Alberta High School </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- A 14-year-old boy opened fire with
a gun at a high school in Alberta, western Canada, Wednesday,
killing one student and seriously injuring another.
</P>
<P>
The suspect, a Grade 9 student who quit the W.R. Myers public
high school, shot down two students both 17 years old and was
taken into custody at the scene by the school resource officer,
said the police.
</P>
<P>
"The loss of a young life is always difficult to accept. But
the senselessness of this act violence makes it even more painful
and all the more difficult to accept and comprehend," said
Canadian Prime Minister Jean Chretien.
</P>
<P>
