<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "Spring City" Ready for World Horticultural Show (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- When dusk fell on this famous "
Spring City" in southwest China, there would be people out in the
streets to spray water or wash the trees on sidewalks by using
firehoses. They were not firemen in drills, but volunteers doing
the last touch of preparations to greet the opening of the '99
Kunming International Horticultural Exposition on May 1.
</P>
<P>
With only two days to go, the people are busy sprucing up the
city, making it as beautiful as it can be.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that five million pots of flowers have been
laid in every major street and lane of the city that has a
population of 3.8 million.
</P>
<P>
"It seems to me that the whole city is a large garden," said
Chen Xiaojuan, a tourist from north China who just bought two
bundles of carnations from a local flower market.
</P>
<P>
The newly-built six-lane road leading from the airport to the
downtown area is decorated with flowers and grass, with colorful
bunting bearing the expo emblem and mascot designs fluttering in
the breeze. Banners inscribed with the expo theme, "Man and Nature,
Marching Into the 21st Century", are strung over major streets,
crossings and overpasses.
</P>
<P>
Facelifting started two years ago when the city was chosen to
be the host of the exposition. The city government has spent more
than two billion yuan (about 250 million US dollars) upgrading 69
streets,laying six large downtown lawns with a total area of 274
hectares and covering 30 percent of the city with green.
</P>
<P>
"The cityscape has changed a lot," exclaimed Jiang Zhenfeng, a
retired worker. "All streets are tidy and clean. Spitting or
cigarette butts are nowhere to be seen."
</P>
<P>
Reputed as China's "Spring City" for its year-round mild
climate, Kunming is believed to be the best choice for hosting the
horticultural show.
</P>
<P>
The large Kunming new airport was completed and put into
service on April 15. It is capable of handling 12 million
passengers a year.
</P>
</TEXT>
