<HEADLINE> Serbian President, Ethnic Albanian Leader Inks Joint Statement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Serbian President Milan
Milutinovic and Kosovo's ethnic Albanian leader Ibrahim Rugova on
Wednesday signed a joint statement in Pristina on seeking a
peaceful solution to the Kosovo issue.
</P>
<P>
The two also agreed in the statement on the need for an
imminent establishment of a temporary government in Kosovo,
reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The statement called on both sides to immediately resume their
negotiations for an early political agreement, which will grant
Kosovo comprehensive self-government with full equality of all
ethnic groups and will respect the territorial integrity and
sovereignty of Serbia and Yugoslavia. Only such an agreement
could lay the foundation for a lasting and just solution to the
Kosovo issue, it said.
</P>
<P>
Both sides noted the negotiations should be "direct" and
involve representatives from all ethnic groups in Kosovo. Direct
negotiations were proof of mutual respect, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
International community representatives could be present at the
negotiations as guests with the agreement of both sides, it added.
</P>
