<HEADLINE> Vietnam Organizations Urge NATO to Stop Attacks Against Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The Vietnam Fatherland Front and
the Vietnam Union of Scientific and Technical Associations (VUSTA)
have strongly condemned the U.S. and NATO's military actions
against Yugoslavia and urged NATO to end its attack against that
country.
</P>
<P>
The Presidium of the Vietnam Fatherland Front said in a
statement Wednesday that the destructive war against Yugoslavia
launched by the U.S. and NATO has outrageously violated the basic
principles of the United Nations Charter, as well as essential
rights of a nation and the right to live of a person, and is
destroying the natural environment.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the Vietnamese people share with the
Yugoslavian people the pain and losses caused by NATO's attack.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnam Fatherland Front has called on the United Nations
Secretary General, all countries, and peace, justice and
progress-loving forces across the world to take concrete and
practical actions to make NATO stop immediately the use of force
against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
In its statement, the Vietnam Union of Scientific and Technical
Associations (VUSTA) demanded the U.S. and its allies stop
immediately and unconditionally all forms of military interference
in Yugoslavia, stressing that their continual bombing of
Yugoslavia since March 24 has killed and injured many innocent
civilians.
</P>
<P>
The VUSTA said the outrageous attack against Yugoslavia, a
sovereign country, by the U.S. and its NATO allies has destroyed
cultural works and the environment, causing heavy losses to the
Yugoslavian people and country, and threatening the cause of peace
in the world.
</P>
<P>
The Union called on scientists and intellectuals all over the
world to raise their voice of conscience and humanity against the
attack on Yugoslavia. 
</P>
