<HEADLINE> Venezuela Seizes 1.5 Tons of Cocaine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Venezuela has seized 1.5 tons of
cocaine coming from Colombia and arrested two people, the
country's anti-narcotics agency said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The cocaine, the largest amount seized in Venezuela so far this
year, was captured at 19:00 local time (23:00 GMT) on Monday
during an operation by the National Guard on Margarita Island.
</P>
<P>
The goods were contained in 50 packages, each weighing 30
kilograms, in the bow and a refrigerated pantry of an expensive
boat in the dockyard of Chacachacare on the Macanao Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
The owner of the boat, Felipe Segundo Durango Garcia, was
detained along with another man whose identity was not given by
the authorities.
</P>
<P>
The cocaine from Colombia was being transported to Europe,
possibly by the drug cartel "Guajira", said a senior official.
</P>
