<HEADLINE> Largest Private Museum Opens in Southwestern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- China's largest private museum
has been opened here in Kunming, capital of southwestern China's
Yunnan province, right before the opening of the China '99 Kunming
International Horticultural Exposition.
</P>
<P>
Located in the southern part of Kunming City, the art museum,
built at a cost of 36 million yuan (about 4.35 million US dollars),
covers nearly three hectares.
</P>
<P>
The whole museum has five exhibition areas, devoted
respectively to paintings and calligraphic works, blue and white
porcelain, purple earthware, ethnic costumes and ornaments, and
fossils and grotesque stones.
</P>
<P>
Ancillary facilities of the museum include a study, a gallery,
an arts and crafts shop and a hotel as well as facilities for
auction and sales promotion.
</P>
<P>
The opening of the museum is part of the Expo '99 activities.
The museum was built by Mr. Luo Huanxin, a local businessman and a
well-known collector. He inherited a large collection left over
from his grandfather and enriched the family collections by
purchasing a wealth of precious paintings and calligraphic works,
porcelain and chinaware with money he earned from his flower
business. 
</P>
</TEXT>
