<HEADLINE> Sino-German Cooperation in Rural Vocational Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, April 29 (Xinhua) -- A Sino-German cooperation
program in rural vocational education was kicked off recently in
the city of Tangshan in north China's Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
The program is expected to do away with outmoded production
methods in the countryside by way of training more qualified rural
people and spreading modern agrotechniques.
</P>
<P>
Germany will pump up six million Deutsch marks to support the
program, which will be carried out in vocational education centers
of Tangshan's five counties.
</P>
<P>
Students there will receive training in specialties ranging
from agronomy, processing of farm and sideline produce, to
agricultural farm machinery.
</P>
<P>
Hebei has witnessed fairly rapid expansion in rural vocational
education. All of the province's 139 counties have set up
vocational education centers, with a combined enrollment of 170,
000 students, according to local sources.  
</P>
