Noting that the current situation in the Balkan region is "very
complicated," he said much work needs to be done.
</P>
<P>
On his part, South African Foreign Minister Alfred Nzo stressed
the U.N. should play a more active role in solving the crisis. As
Non-Aligned Movement (NAM) president, he added, South Africa
called on the movement to play its due role in the crisis.
</P>
<P>
Nzo arrived here Wednesday with President Nelson Mandela on a
state visit.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, it is reported Russian president's envoy to Kosovo
Viktor Chernomyrdin will leave for Germany, Italy and Yugoslavia
on Thursday for mediation. Earlier, he stated that the stop of the
NATO bombardment is the requisite for the beginning of a political
solution to the crisis. 
