<HEADLINE> Panamanian Party Condemns NATO Strikes Against Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The Panamanian People's Party
(PPP) urged all the social sectors of the country to declare
themselves against the military attacks by NATO against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The PPP said on Wednesday that the military action led by the U.
S. against the government of Slobodan Milosevic violates human
rights and is a criminal act.
</P>
<P>
The party said that under the pretext of human rights, the
military intervention by NATO in Yugoslavia was hypocritical.
</P>
<P>
The PPP stated that each bombing raid cost 334 million U.S.
dollars, a figure sufficient to repair the damage caused to
Central America last year by natural disasters.
</P>
<P>
The party believed that NATO's military actions were sheer
proof of their hegemonism, to which no Latin American country
could stay silent.
</P>
<P>
It also said that the imperialism of the U.S. and its European
allies against Yugoslavia, must be rejected by all social sectors,
and by every person with common sense and true humanity. 
</P>
