<BODY>
<HEADLINE> M.Slamet in Indonesian Central Java Becoming Dangerous </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Mount Slamet in Indonesia's
Central Java province is displaying increased activities and the
local population has been warned of the impending danger and
mountaineering discouraged, Antara News Agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The volcano's increased activities began on April 19, 1999 and
the temperature on the slopes was rising driving animals down
slopes toward residential areas.
</P>
<P>
The mountain is located on the border of the regencies of
Pemalang, Tegal, Brebes and Banyumas in the province.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Sukedi, head of the Mount Slamet
observation post in Pemalang district, observed the threatening
developments from his post and told the local administration to
close mountaineering gates.
</P>
<P>
Munir, head of the Pemalang district, said the volcano has
become a serious threat, and urged local people to stay alert and
ready for evacuation if the situation worsened. 
</P>
</TEXT>
