<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Foreign Exchange Reserves Decline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's net foreign exchange
reserves dropped to 15.81 billion U.S. dollars on April 23 from
15.86 billion U.S. dollars on April 15, The Jakarta Post reported
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The slight fall in net foreign exchange reserves was due to the
repayment of foreign loans, Bank Indonesia said in its latest
weekly report.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, Bank Indonesia said the level was still above the
International Monetary Fund's adjusted net international reserves
target of 14.3 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Gross international reserves -- net foreign exchange reserves
plus outstanding foreign exchange contracts -- also fell to 25.80
billion U.S. dollars on April 23 from 25.84 billion U.S. dollars
on April 15, the central bank said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
