<DOCNO> XIE19990429.0328 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Grieving Mia Skips Simulation Match after Mother's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's best women's shuttler
Mia Audina was forced to pull out of a simulation match on
Wednesday for the Sudirman Cup and World Championships after her
mother died from a stroke in the morning, The Jakarta Post
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Mia was still in shock and unable to give interviews following
her mother's death at 8:50 a.m. local time on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Mia's mother Lanny Susilawati suffered from kidney failure and
underwent weekly hemodialysis.
</P>
<P>
Badminton Association of Indonesia (PBSI) vice chairman Agus
Wirahadikusumah told reporters during the simulation that PBSI was
deeply saddened by Mia's loss.
</P>
<P>
"We will understand if Mia is still in shock in the next few
weeks. It depends on PBSI chairman (Subagyo Hadisiswoyo) to decide
whether we will send Mia to Copenhagen (World Championships) or
not. In the future, we hope Mia will be able to overcome her grief
and boost her fighting spirit," he said.
</P>
<P>
PBSI officials will hold a special meeting to discuss Mia's
condition.
</P>
<P>
In Wednesday's simulation, men's singles Taufik Hidayat beat
senior Budi Santoso 12-15, 17-14, 15-6, and Hendrawan defeated
veteran Hariyanto Arbi 15-9, 15-10. In the women's singles, Ellen
Angelina eliminated Lidya Djaelawidjaja 8-11, 11-1, 13-12.
</P>
<P>
In the men's doubles, veterans Ricky Subagja and Rexy Mainaky
overcame All England champions Candra Wijaya and Tony Gunawan 8-15,
15-13, 15-9. World number one Flandy Limpele and Eng Hian beat
seniors Antonius and Denny Kantono 12-15, 15-8, 15-10.
</P>
<P>
In the women's doubles, Indarti Issoliana and Deyana Lombana
were forced to default to Cynthia Tuwankotta and Etty Tantri 15-11,
11-15, 0-3 after Indarti injured her back. Deyana and Carmelita
beat Vita Marissa and Cynthia 15-5, 9-15, 15-8.
</P>
<P>
The veteran mixed doubles team of Tri Kusherjanto and Minarti
Timur defeated Wahyu Agung and Emma Ermawati 15-7, 15-4, and the
new partnership of Imam Tohari and Vita lost to Bambang Suprianto
and Zelin Resiana 2-15, 14-17. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
