<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cambodian FM Leaves for Hanoi Admission Ceremony </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Foreign Minister Hor
Nam Hong left here Thursday morning for Hanoi, Vietnam to attend
the ceremony to admit Cambodia into the Association of Southeast
Asian Nations (ASEAN).
</P>
<P>
The ceremony will be held in Hanoi on Friday to admit Cambodia
into ASEAN as its 10th member, which will finally fulfill the
dream of bringing all the 10 countries in the region into the
regional grouping.
</P>
<P>
Hor Nam Hong told the reporters at the airport that "April 30
will become a day of historic significance as the vision of
10-ASEAN has come true."
</P>
<P>
"Cambodia's entry into ASEAN serves the interests and needs of
both Cambodia and ASEAN. With Cambodia's entry, ASEAN will become
a more powerful regional grouping politically and economically,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
"We have made a lot of efforts and preparations for joining the
regional group, because it will bring great political and economic
benefits to Cambodia," he added.
</P>
<P>
"Though Cambodia will face many difficulties after joining
ASEAN," he said, "We are optimistic about the future."
</P>
<P>
During the ceremony, Hor Nam Hong will sign two agreements --
the declaration to join ASEAN and the recognition of all ASEAN
agreements.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam will host the special admission ceremony for Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia had been scheduled to join ASEAN on July 23, 1997
along with Laos and Myanmar, but the plan was put on hold after
factional fighting broke out in Phnom Penh. 
</P>
</TEXT>
