<HEADLINE> Yugoslav Vice Prime Minister Sacked for Deviating Statements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslav Prime Minister Momir
Bulatovic Wednesday sacked Deputy Prime Minister Vuk Draskovic for
"openly opposing the government's position and undermining its
credibility", the Ministry of Information said.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference held on Tuesday to mark the seventh
anniversary of the founding of the Yugoslav Federation, Draskovic,
who assumed the deputy premiership on January 22, accused the
Yugoslav ruling party, the Social Party of Serbia, of
strengthening dictatorship by taking advantage of the current war
status.
</P>
<P>
The Belgrade Independence Television Station controlled by
Draskovic-led opposition party, the Serbian Renewal Movement, gave
the press conference a live broadcast.
</P>
<P>
On the same occasion, Draskovic also welcomed the stationing of
multinational peace-keeping forces in Kosovo under the control of
the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslav Foreign Ministry spokesman Nebojsa Vujevic reiterated
on Wednesday that "the Yugoslav Federation will only accept
unarmed civilian monitors to be sent to Kosovo by the United
Nations." 
</P>
