<HEADLINE> TAT Targets Potential Tourists Using Cyberspace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The Tourism Authority of Thailand
(TAT) has announced a niche market strategy, using Internet
information technology to attract potential tourists.
</P>
<P>
TAT would invest 26 million baht (702,702 U.S. dollars) in the
development of an Internet Web page to attract visitors from
lucrative markets, particularly from North America and Japan, TAT
deputy governor Juthamas Siriwan was quoted Thursday by The Nation
as saying.
</P>
<P>
She said a great number of American and Japanese tourists spend
many hours surfing the Net For travel information and the TAT's
new Web page, which will display Thai tourist attractions, will be
targeted at those groups.
</P>
<P>
The Web page is part of the TAT's overall plan for niche market
promotional campaigns.
</P>
<P>
Juthamas said that more than a half of the amount allocated
would be directed towards promoting the U.S. market, from which
the number of tourists to Thailand in 1998 grew by 17.8 percent to
415,831 on a year-on-year basis. 
</P>
