<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Special Park for Students Back from Abroad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 29 (Xinhua) -- A special industrial
development park is to be set up in Guangzhou, capital city of
south China's Guangdong Province, for Chinese students who have
returned from abroad to establish businesses.
</P>
<P>
A dozen returned students have applied to settle their research
projects in the park within the Guangzhou Economic and
Technological Development Zone, local authorities said.
</P>
<P>
The park, covering an area of 200 mu (15 mu equals one hectare),
will provide a series of preferential treatments for investors. A
legal system will be introduced to protect intellectual property
rights of the investors and a training center for postgraduates
and doctors will also be set up there.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou, an economically advantaged metropolis, expects the
effort to speed up the development of its high-tech industry.
</P>
</TEXT>
