<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mourning Has Slight Eye Fracture, out Two Weeks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Miami Heat star center Alonzo
Mourning is in need of a new facial device to protect his injured
right eye and will be sidelined for at least two games.
</P>
<P>
Examinations today by Heat team doctors revealed a slight
fracture of Mourning's right eye orbit, but surgery is not
necessary.
</P>
<P>
He has been ruled out of Miami's next games Thursday against
Boston and Saturday versus Chicago. However, Mourning could be
available to play when the Heat host the Charlotte Hornets on
Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
The four-time All-Star center suffered the injury when he was
poked in the eye in Monday's 90-65 win at Cleveland and missed
Tuesday's 95-76 victory at New Jersey.
</P>
<P>
Mourning is no stranger to injury, having missed an average of
nearly 14 games over his first six seasons. Last year, he wore a
protective mask that covered most of his face after breaking his
left cheekbone.
</P>
<P>
This time around, Mourning will wear a device to protect the
eye when he returns to action.
</P>
<P>
The injury comes at a bad time for the Heat, who are battling
for the top seed in the Eastern Conference. At 31-14, they lead
Orlando by two games for the Atlantic Division lead and Indiana,
the front-runner in the Central Division, by 2 1/2 games with five
to play.
</P>
<P>
Mourning leads the league in blocked shots at 4.0 per game, is
12th in scoring (20.3), seventh in rebounds (11.1) and ninth in
field-goal percentage (.511). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
