<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Norway on Way to Euro Soccer Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Norway trounced Georgia 4-1 in
Tbilisi on Wednesday in a European Soccer Championships group two
qualifying match on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Austria blanked San Marino 7-0, restoring national
pride after the 9-0 crush by Spain last month and taking them to
the top of group six.
</P>
<P>
All Norway's goals came from players currently with teams in
the English premier league with Chelsea's Tore Andre Flo scoring
twice, and Tottenham Hotspur's Steffen Iversen and Ole Gunnar
Solskjaer of Manchester United adding the others.
</P>
<P>
Norway raced into a 4-0 lead after only 38 minutes but failed
to take greater advantage of a weak Georgian side who scored a
consolation goal midway through the second half.
</P>
<P>
With Latvia, the leaders at the start of the day, being held to
a 0-0 draw at home by Albania in a match switched to Riga because
of the situation in the Balkans, Norway moved two points clear at
the top of group two.
</P>
<P>
They lead with 10 points from five matches, followed by Latvia
with eight from five and Greece six from five.
</P>
<P>
Slovenia, Georgia and Albania occupy the bottom three places
and are all but out of the running.
</P>
<P>
Out of a job is Georgia's coach Vladimir Gutsayev who announced
his intention to quit after this match a month ago claiming he
could not get on with several players in the team.
</P>
<P>
Ivica Vastic scored three goals for Austria, with Christian
Maryleb scoring twice. Martin Amerhauser and the veteran Andreas
Herzog (penalty) scored the others.
</P>
<P>
Austria, under new Croatian coach Otto Baric, go back to the
top of a very tight group with 10 points from five matches. They
are a point clear of Spain, who have nine points from four matches,
and surprise package Cyprus who have nine points from five matches.
</P>
<P>
Israel have seven points from four games, while San Marino are
bottom after six straight defeats and a goal tally of 1-27.
</P>
</TEXT>
