<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Vietnam to Launch Joint Oil Search </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- China and Viet Nam will work at
strengthening their bilateral co-cooperation in offshore oil
exploration, today's China Daily quoted a China National Offshore
Oil Corp (CNOOC) source as saying.
</P>
<P>
The papers said that Peprovietnam, a large-scale Vietnamese
state-owned company engaged in the offshore oil exploration
business, will invite international public bidding for a
polyethylene extracting project worth 80 million US dollars and a
2 million-ton gas storage project.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese government has invited the CNOOC to participate
in the public bidding and hopes for mutual co-operation in the
offshore oil and gas exploration field.
</P>
<P>
The CNOOC officials said that they will send a specialist group
to Viet Nam to assess the economic efficiency of the projects
involved and discuss the co-operation possibilities between the
two groups.
</P>
<P>
In addition, CNOOC would like to take practical measures to
forge a healthy business relationship with its Vietnamese
counterpart in many areas, including technical exchanges and
professional training programs.
</P>
<P>
Recently, a Peprovietnam delegation paid a formal visit to
CNOOC. At the talks, also attended by the Vietnamese ambassador to
China, the two sides briefed each other on their business
development outlines.
</P>
<P>
Both sides agreed that the two countries have bright co-
operation prospects in the oil exploration business in the future.
</P>
<P>
The CNOOC is interested in the offshore oil and gas exploration
with its priorities in providing technology and equipment, said
the officials.
</P>
<P>
Peprovieetnam is making efforts to expand international co-
operation and is seeking technical exchange opportunities with
their overseas counterparts.
</P>
<P>
The top officials of the two countries wish the boundary
division problem in Beibu Bay will be solved as soon as possible
to speed up the bilateral business co-operation process.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, the Peprovietnam delegation looked around the
offshore oil exploration research center with senior consultants
of CNOOC.
</P>
<P>
Since 1997, the two countries' industrial organizations have
broken the ice and begun to get in touch with each other. The
recent visit and the bilateral talks have stepped up the pace in
the two-way co-operation, officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
