<HEADLINE> London Police Arrest Gunman After Siege </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Armed police stormed a flat and
arrested a man Wednesday evening after a chase through the streets
of west London and a brief siege.
</P>
<P>
Police said a family of three had been trapped in the flat
above during the siege, but they were not held hostage and were
unharmed.
</P>
<P>
The drama began around 16:20 local time (1520 GMT) when a man,
driving a blue Maestro car, left a petrol station without paying.
</P>
<P>
He was pursued by police and opened fire on a police car before
hijacking another car.
</P>
<P>
The suspect, said to be armed with both an assault rifle and a
pistol, drove towards the High Street of nearby Feltham, where he
abandoned the Maestro.
</P>
<P>
The gunman then stopped and got into a white Vauxhall Astra. He
later abandoned the car and fled on foot, police said.
</P>
<P>
At around 19:30, he took over a ground floor flat in Feltham in
west London where a family of three people were living.
</P>
<P>
Police sieged the house, negotiated in vain and then stormed
into it to arrest the gunman. Nobody was believed to have been
hurt in the incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
