<HEADLINE> Clinton to Visit Germany Early in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 28 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
will fly to Germany Tuesday to meet U.S. pilots bombing Yugoslavia
and troops aiding hundreds of thousands of refugees from the
Kosovo conflict.
</P>
<P>
"He'll be traveling to Spangdahlem... to visit with American
combat pilots and will also visit Ramstein... to see the base's
humanitarian relief operation," White House spokesman Nanda Chitre
told reporters.
</P>
<P>
It will be the first time for Clinton to see U.S. troops since
the U.S.-led NATO began bombing Yugoslavia on March 24.
</P>
<P>
Clinton is due to leave Washington late Tuesday and to return
either late Wednesday or early Thursday, Chitre said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman also said that another stop might be added to the
trip. 
</P>
</TEXT>
