<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kosovo War Threatens Macedonian Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Macedonian Finance Minister Boris
Stojmenov said Wednesday that the on-going Kosovo war is
threatening the economic stability in Macedonia and ruining the
prospect of the country's development.
</P>
<P>
Stojmenov told foreign reporters that due to the Kosovo war,
Macedonia's economy is facing a very grave situation with the
national gross product (NGP) expected to decline by 8 percent and
the budget deficit-NGP rate to rise from the originally planned
0.1 percent to 4.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Unless Macedonia can have 485 million U.S. dollars in foreign
aid, it cannot maintain the economic stability, he said.
</P>
<P>
An economic slowdown in Macedonia will threaten the stability
not only in Macedonia but also in the entire Balkan region, the
Macedonian minister warned.
</P>
<P>
The Macedonian economy has been adversely affected by NATO air
strikes on Yugoslavia which began on March 24.
</P>
<P>
The Macedonian government said that the economic loss caused by
the Kosovo war will amount to 1.5 billion U.S. dollars by the end
of this year.
</P>
<P>
Macedonia has called on the international community, especially
the Western countries, for financial assistance and writing off or
delaying the payment of its foreign debts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
